WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:04.128
[ popping ]

00:04.213 --> 00:06.255
- [ sighs ]
- Hey, Rick.

00:06.340 --> 00:08.257
I have to make a project for
the science fair this weekend.

00:08.342 --> 00:09.926
You think you could help me out?

00:10.010 --> 00:11.730
- Whatever.
- Well, I mean, traditionally...

00:11.804 --> 00:14.180
science fairs are
a father-son thing.

00:14.264 --> 00:17.058
Well, scientifically,
traditions are an idiot thing.

00:17.142 --> 00:18.643
Morty, I think it would
be fun for you

00:18.727 --> 00:21.479
to work on a science project
with your Dad.

00:21.563 --> 00:23.439
[ cellphone beeps ]

00:23.524 --> 00:25.441
Uh...
[ clears throat ]

00:25.526 --> 00:28.194
Yeah, Dad.
Why don't we do it together?

00:28.278 --> 00:31.072
Yes! You backed the right horse
on this one, son.

00:31.156 --> 00:33.282
We'll get out the crayons,
brew some coffee,

00:33.367 --> 00:35.702
and knock this thing out
in two or three days.

00:35.786 --> 00:37.078
[ robot whirs ]

00:37.162 --> 00:38.621
[ monotone ] What is my purpose?

00:38.706 --> 00:40.873
Pass the butter.

00:42.376 --> 00:43.960
Thank you.

00:44.044 --> 00:45.628
[ popping ]

00:45.713 --> 00:46.796
[ sighs ]

00:46.880 --> 00:48.339
Dad, I need a ride to work.

00:48.424 --> 00:50.216
Maybe Rick can give you a ride.

00:50.300 --> 00:52.093
I'm helping Morty with science.

00:52.177 --> 00:54.095
- I'm busy.
- Doing what?

00:54.179 --> 00:56.639
Uh, anything else.

00:56.724 --> 00:58.641
What is my purpose?

00:58.726 --> 01:00.768
You pass butter.

01:00.853 --> 01:02.478
Oh, my god.

01:02.563 --> 01:04.522
Yeah, welcome to the club, pal.

01:38.849 --> 01:40.391
Since when do you have a job?

01:40.476 --> 01:41.476
Since last week.

01:41.477 --> 01:43.227
It's part-time at this
little vintage thrift store.

01:43.312 --> 01:45.646
My boss is this really
smart, eccentric old man

01:45.731 --> 01:47.940
that treats me nice
and values me.

01:48.025 --> 01:49.817
Meow.
Can't wait to meet...

01:49.902 --> 01:51.694
this [burps]
fascinating character.

01:51.779 --> 01:54.322
Please don't.

01:54.406 --> 01:57.200
Oh. Well, when did this
stop being Jamba Juice?

01:57.284 --> 01:59.452
I've just recently opened
for business,

01:59.536 --> 02:01.621
Mister, um, Goldenfold.

02:01.705 --> 02:02.997
You know my name?

02:03.081 --> 02:04.791
[ chuckling ] That's disarming.

02:04.875 --> 02:07.627
I also know you long
for female company.

02:07.711 --> 02:10.755
You know, it has been
lonely since the divorce.

02:10.839 --> 02:13.674
Some voids can't be filled
with Jamba Juice.

02:13.759 --> 02:17.261
This aftershave makes a
man quite irresistible to women.

02:17.346 --> 02:18.721
Free of charge.

02:18.806 --> 02:21.432
One never pays here...
not with money.

02:21.517 --> 02:23.434
Nothing to read into
there. Thanks!

02:23.519 --> 02:25.478
Sorry I'm late,
Mr. Needful.

02:25.562 --> 02:28.731
This is my grandpa, Rick.
He was just leaving.

02:28.816 --> 02:29.857
Huh.

02:29.942 --> 02:31.734
Tell me, Rick,
what do you desire?

02:31.819 --> 02:33.736
Eh, I make my own stuff.

02:33.821 --> 02:35.613
So, what are you...
like, the devil?

02:35.697 --> 02:37.281
- What? Sorry?
- I don't know.

02:37.366 --> 02:40.493
Store comes out of nowhere,
all the shit's old and creepy.

02:40.577 --> 02:42.453
Are you the devil?
A demon? Leprechaun?

02:42.538 --> 02:44.330
- Grandpa Rick!
- Hey, I'm not judging.

02:44.414 --> 02:46.332
Just like shoot straight.
I'm a man of science.

02:46.416 --> 02:49.168
Ah, then perhaps you could
make use of this.

02:49.253 --> 02:53.172
This microscope reveals things
beyond comprehension.

02:53.257 --> 02:54.465
[ laughs ]

02:54.550 --> 02:56.008
[ Rick laughs ]

02:56.093 --> 02:56.884
[ laughs louder ]

02:56.969 --> 02:58.094
[ Rick laughs louder ]

02:58.178 --> 02:59.470
[ laughs louder ]

02:59.555 --> 03:00.555
[ Rick laughs louder ]

03:00.597 --> 03:01.472
[ laughs louder ]

03:01.557 --> 03:03.474
Grandpa, go home and drink.

03:03.559 --> 03:05.309
[ swoop! ]

03:05.394 --> 03:07.311
Why don't we do a model
of the solar system?

03:07.396 --> 03:09.396
That's what my Dad did with me
when I was your age.

03:09.398 --> 03:10.898
Oh, okay.

03:10.983 --> 03:13.568
You know, Rick's in his lab,
making cyborgs

03:13.652 --> 03:15.903
and wormholes
and all that weird stuff,

03:15.988 --> 03:17.738
but this is real science.

03:17.823 --> 03:19.907
A man and his boy,
making planets.

03:19.992 --> 03:22.493
Hey, how about we use
a ping-pong ball for Pluto?

03:22.578 --> 03:23.953
And then Jupiter...

03:24.037 --> 03:26.539
Uh, actually, I don't
think Pluto's a planet.

03:26.623 --> 03:28.040
[ chuckles ]

03:28.125 --> 03:29.917
Of course Pluto's a planet, son.

03:30.002 --> 03:31.794
I learned that
in the third grade.

03:31.879 --> 03:33.546
Well, yeah, but you
know they changed it.

03:33.630 --> 03:35.506
Morty, nobody changed
the planets.

03:35.591 --> 03:37.925
I just googled it.
Pluto's not a planet.

03:38.010 --> 03:39.927
They changed it in 2006.

03:40.012 --> 03:42.638
Yeah, I heard about that, Morty.

03:42.723 --> 03:45.516
And I disagree.
- You disagree?

03:45.601 --> 03:48.019
That's right. It's possible
to disagree in science, Morty.

03:48.103 --> 03:49.687
Pluto was a planet.

03:49.771 --> 03:51.411
Some committee of
fancy assholes disagree.

03:51.440 --> 03:53.357
I disagree back.
Give me a ping-pong ball.

03:53.442 --> 03:55.818
Um, okay.
I-I just have to...

03:55.903 --> 03:57.663
Go find Rick and go
over my head about Pluto?

03:57.738 --> 03:58.863
No. Geez!

03:58.947 --> 04:01.282
I just gotta go
to the bathroom. Damn.

04:01.366 --> 04:04.160
Oh. [ coughs ]
Okay, good.

04:04.244 --> 04:05.828
[ laughing ]
This is gonna be fun.

04:05.913 --> 04:06.913
[ electricity crackling ]

04:06.914 --> 04:08.714
Hey, Morty, let me [burps]...
let me [burps]...

04:08.749 --> 04:10.583
let me ask you a question
real quick.

04:10.667 --> 04:12.418
Does evil exist, and if so,

04:12.502 --> 04:14.170
can one detect and measure it?

04:14.254 --> 04:16.005
- Um...
- Rhetorical question, Morty.

04:16.089 --> 04:18.382
The answer's "yes, you just
have to be a genius."

04:18.467 --> 04:20.301
Cute. Your sister's boss
gave me a microscope

04:20.385 --> 04:21.886
that would have
made me retarded.

04:21.970 --> 04:23.679
Ooh.
Oh, boy, Rick.

04:23.764 --> 04:25.681
I'm don't think you're allowed
to say that word, you know?

04:25.766 --> 04:28.059
Morty, I'm not disparaging
the differently abled.

04:28.143 --> 04:30.478
I'm stating the fact that
if I had used this microscope,

04:30.562 --> 04:32.122
it would have made me
mentally retarded.

04:32.189 --> 04:34.565
Okay, yeah, but I don't think
it's about logic, Rick.

04:34.650 --> 04:36.484
I think the word has just
become a symbolic issue for

04:36.568 --> 04:38.986
powerful groups that are
doing the right thing.

04:39.071 --> 04:40.696
Well, that's retarded.

04:40.781 --> 04:42.573
- What are you talking about?
- Apparently, nothing.

04:42.658 --> 04:44.617
You asked him if
Pluto's a planet, didn't you?

04:44.701 --> 04:45.701
- No!
- It's not.

04:45.786 --> 04:47.203
- Shut up, Rick.
- Whoa.

04:47.287 --> 04:48.871
I don't care what anyone says.

04:48.956 --> 04:51.707
If it can be a planet,
it can be a planet again.

04:51.792 --> 04:54.627
Planet.
Planet, planet, planet.

04:54.711 --> 04:57.129
Stay scientific, Jerry.

04:58.840 --> 05:00.758
This aftershave made women
want me,

05:00.842 --> 05:02.760
but it also made me impotent!

05:02.844 --> 05:05.471
A price for everything,
Mr. Goldenfold.

05:05.555 --> 05:07.807
A price for everything.

05:07.891 --> 05:09.141
[ laughs evilly ]

05:09.226 --> 05:11.519
[ gasps ] Oh, my god!

05:11.603 --> 05:14.230
How could I not
see this coming?!

05:14.314 --> 05:17.984
[ sobbing ] My lust!

05:18.068 --> 05:20.194
My greed!

05:20.278 --> 05:22.780
I deserved this!

05:22.864 --> 05:25.783
This serum should [burps]
counteract the negative effects.

05:25.867 --> 05:28.494
Holy cats!
Ladies, let's get out of here.

05:28.578 --> 05:30.496
[ door opens ]
I haven't learned a thing!

05:30.580 --> 05:31.914
Here. [burps]

05:31.999 --> 05:33.666
You can have this [burps] back.

05:33.750 --> 05:34.917
You didn't use it?

05:35.002 --> 05:36.794
Sure I did...
to develop this.

05:36.878 --> 05:38.879
It detects and catalogs
all your "Twilight Zone,"

05:38.964 --> 05:41.382
Ray Bradbury,
"Friday the 13th" The Series

05:41.466 --> 05:43.050
voodoo crap magic.

05:43.135 --> 05:44.552
I thought you might
want it so you didn't

05:44.636 --> 05:47.054
accidentally
sell anybody, say...

05:47.139 --> 05:49.598
A typewriter that generates
best-selling murder mysteries

05:49.683 --> 05:52.518
and then makes the murders
happen in real life?

05:52.602 --> 05:53.477
Ooh.
- Be quiet.

05:53.562 --> 05:54.895
Don't you want to make sure

05:54.980 --> 05:56.480
people know what they're
getting?

05:56.565 --> 05:58.607
You're not intentionally
selling...

05:58.692 --> 06:00.401
Beauty cream that makes
ugly ladies pretty

06:00.485 --> 06:02.653
but also makes them blind?

06:02.738 --> 06:04.655
I find this all quite
preposterous.

06:04.740 --> 06:06.657
Oh, I say, good sir.
Oh, harrumph.

06:06.742 --> 06:09.618
Oh, oh [babbles]!

06:09.703 --> 06:11.120
That's beautiful.

06:11.204 --> 06:13.956
You know it's gonna be wearing
you in three hours?

06:14.041 --> 06:15.761
[ door opens ]
Do I need to call the police?

06:15.792 --> 06:17.126
Here, you can use my phone.

06:17.210 --> 06:18.669
Don't worry, it won't
make you deaf

06:18.754 --> 06:20.004
because I'm not a hack.

06:20.088 --> 06:21.422
Hey!

06:21.506 --> 06:23.007
[ both grunting ]

06:23.091 --> 06:24.467
You think you're fucking
so great!

06:24.551 --> 06:26.343
Stop it! No!

06:26.428 --> 06:28.220
Fuck yeah, man.

06:28.305 --> 06:29.972
Stop it right now!

06:30.057 --> 06:32.058
Grandpa Rick,
I like working here.

06:32.142 --> 06:34.226
- You work for the devil.
- So what?

06:34.311 --> 06:35.895
- BOTH: "So what?"
- Yes!

06:35.979 --> 06:37.563
So what if he's the devil, Rick?

06:37.647 --> 06:39.231
At least the devil has a job.

06:39.316 --> 06:40.983
At least he's active
in the community.

06:41.068 --> 06:42.651
What do you do?

06:42.736 --> 06:44.737
You eat our food
and make gadgets.

06:44.821 --> 06:47.114
Buh-bye.

06:47.199 --> 06:48.616
Wh[burps]Oops.

06:48.700 --> 06:50.534
[ giggles ]

06:50.619 --> 06:52.703
I'm sorry, Mr. Needful.
I'll clean that up.

06:52.788 --> 06:54.497
I don't know what I can do
about the ghost lady

06:54.581 --> 06:56.165
that came out of it, but...
- It's fine.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.125
Summer, you know,
your grandfather's right.

06:58.210 --> 07:00.920
This store curses people.
That's my business.

07:01.004 --> 07:03.339
Well, yeah.
Fast-food gives people diabetes,

07:03.423 --> 07:05.174
and clothing stores have
sweatshops.

07:05.258 --> 07:07.384
Is there a company hiring
teenagers that isn't evil?

07:07.469 --> 07:09.095
This is my first job.

07:09.179 --> 07:10.805
You've been nice to me,
Mr. Needful.

07:10.889 --> 07:12.598
You respect me.

07:12.682 --> 07:15.101
Please, call me "The Devil."

07:15.185 --> 07:16.936
I'd rather not, actually.

07:17.020 --> 07:18.771
Yes, perhaps not during
business hours.

07:18.855 --> 07:20.773
I told you, I want to
file a declaration

07:20.857 --> 07:22.942
that Pluto is a planet.

07:23.026 --> 07:25.277
Well, then my son's going to
fail his science class,

07:25.362 --> 07:27.488
and when that happens,
I'm suing you first.

07:27.572 --> 07:28.614
[ clicks ]

07:28.698 --> 07:30.825
I think I know what the "A"
in N.A.S.A. stands for.

07:30.909 --> 07:33.702
- Dad, what's your endgame?
- Ain't no game, sucka.

07:33.787 --> 07:35.454
Why don't we just make the solar
system with eight planets?

07:35.539 --> 07:36.747
It's even easier.

07:36.832 --> 07:39.917
Sure, sure, and why don't we
just burn Galileo at the stake

07:40.001 --> 07:41.919
for saying the sun is round?

07:42.003 --> 07:44.130
Science isn't always easy,
Morty.

07:44.214 --> 07:45.214
[ humming ]

07:45.257 --> 07:47.341
Whoa! Whoa!

07:47.425 --> 07:48.968
What the hell?!

07:49.052 --> 07:52.179
[ both groaning ]

07:52.264 --> 07:54.014
[ ting! ]

07:58.687 --> 08:00.437
[ hisses, buzzes ]

08:00.522 --> 08:02.189
[ fanfare plays ]

08:02.274 --> 08:04.400
I'm King Flippy Nips,
ruler of Pluto.

08:04.484 --> 08:06.735
We discovered you quite
by accident

08:06.820 --> 08:09.405
during routine surveillance
of your world.

08:09.489 --> 08:12.449
You really gave it to those
guys at N.A.S.A.

08:12.534 --> 08:13.951
I was... you know,

08:14.035 --> 08:16.287
sometimes science is
about conviction.

08:16.371 --> 08:18.789
It'd like to introduce you
to a few people

08:18.874 --> 08:20.791
that very much agree with you.

08:20.876 --> 08:22.626
Oh, I...

08:22.711 --> 08:24.920
[ echoing ] Plutonians.

08:25.005 --> 08:26.964
Jerry Smith is a scientist
from Earth,

08:27.048 --> 08:30.467
where he's creating a model
of our solar system.

08:30.552 --> 08:33.804
Jerry, tell Pluto
about your decision.

08:33.889 --> 08:35.389
[ clears throat ]

08:35.473 --> 08:38.017
[ echoing ]
Um... Pluto's a planet.

08:38.101 --> 08:39.310
[ cheers and applause ]

08:39.394 --> 08:42.271
Pluto's a fucking planet, bitch!

08:42.355 --> 08:45.816
Oh, man. This is definitely
gonna go to his head.

08:45.901 --> 08:49.612
If it's athletic prowess
you desire, Principal Vagina,

08:49.696 --> 08:51.488
I might...
- I'll take it.

08:51.573 --> 08:52.573
B-But I haven't even...

08:52.616 --> 08:53.656
Thank you very, very much.

08:53.700 --> 08:55.826
Great store.
Great place. Bye.

08:55.911 --> 08:57.703
Huh. Okay.

08:57.787 --> 09:00.623
I must say, Summer, I thought
your grandfather's outburst

09:00.707 --> 09:01.999
would have disrupted business,

09:02.083 --> 09:04.710
but this is the best weekend
I've had since Salem.

09:04.794 --> 09:06.712
Nice. "Wholesome Delight"
for lunch?

09:06.796 --> 09:08.714
- Is that the vegan place?
- Yeah, I love their soup.

09:08.798 --> 09:10.591
I'm kind of soup-ed out.

09:10.675 --> 09:12.509
[ door opens ]
Mrs. Tate, is it?

09:12.594 --> 09:14.720
What do you desire?

09:14.804 --> 09:16.889
Whoa, whoa, slow down, honey.

09:16.973 --> 09:18.641
Oh, is there a limit?
Everything's free, right?

09:18.725 --> 09:22.269
Let's just say you
don't pay... with money.

09:22.354 --> 09:24.271
[ both chuckle ]
That was perfect.

09:24.356 --> 09:26.273
You pay with the curses, right?

09:26.358 --> 09:27.858
Um... I... well...

09:27.943 --> 09:31.111
But, Mrs. Tate, why do you
want cursed items?

09:31.196 --> 09:32.821
Well, I'm going to get
the curses removed

09:32.906 --> 09:34.156
at "Curse Purge Plus."

09:34.241 --> 09:36.158
You know, the guy on TV?

09:36.243 --> 09:38.202
[ door closes ] What?

09:38.286 --> 09:40.663
Have you acquired
creepy specific old stuff

09:40.747 --> 09:42.164
from a mysterious antique
or thrift store

09:42.249 --> 09:44.583
that gives you powers
but fucks with you

09:44.668 --> 09:45.751
in unforeseeable ways?

09:45.835 --> 09:47.461
Bring it
to "Curse Purge Plus."

09:47.545 --> 09:50.547
[burps] I use science to
UN-curse the items for cash,

09:50.632 --> 09:52.132
and you get to keep the powers.

09:52.217 --> 09:53.497
This guy got mysterious sneakers

09:53.510 --> 09:55.678
to make him run faster,
but guess what?

09:55.762 --> 09:57.554
He would have had to run
until he died,

09:57.639 --> 09:58.764
making them worthless.

09:58.848 --> 10:00.432
I removed the curse,
making them worth,

10:00.517 --> 10:02.726
like, I don't know, $8 million.

10:02.811 --> 10:03.978
See you at the Olympics.

10:04.062 --> 10:05.479
This eerily intelligent doll

10:05.563 --> 10:07.189
was threatening to murder
its family.

10:07.274 --> 10:08.607
Now it does their taxes.

10:08.692 --> 10:10.234
Everything's deductible.

10:10.318 --> 10:11.944
Don't pay for cool stuff
with your soul.

10:12.028 --> 10:13.487
Pay for it with money.

10:13.571 --> 10:15.823
You know, like how every other
store in the world works?

10:15.907 --> 10:18.075
We're located at First and Main
in Old Town.

10:18.159 --> 10:19.493
Come on... come on down.

10:19.577 --> 10:20.786
"First and..."

10:20.870 --> 10:22.079
[ babbles ]

10:22.163 --> 10:24.790
That's right across the street
from "Needful Things,"

10:24.874 --> 10:27.209
where you can get evil items
for free!

10:27.294 --> 10:30.671
Diabolic son of a motherf...

10:30.755 --> 10:32.673
We're back on
"Good Morning, Pluto."

10:32.757 --> 10:34.675
And a very good morning it is

10:34.759 --> 10:37.428
for our guest,
Earth scientist Jerry Smith,

10:37.512 --> 10:39.638
who's making headlines
with his bold announcement

10:39.723 --> 10:41.807
that is what, Jerry?

10:41.891 --> 10:43.475
Pluto is a planet.

10:43.560 --> 10:45.269
[ chuckling ]
Well, how about that.

10:45.353 --> 10:47.271
I love it.
[ cheers and applause ]

10:47.355 --> 10:49.690
Morty Smith.
I'm Scroopy Noopers.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.817
I'm a scientist.
Can I show you something?

10:51.901 --> 10:53.694
Uh, I better not.

10:53.778 --> 10:56.155
Right now.

10:56.239 --> 10:57.114
[ blurp! ]

10:57.198 --> 10:58.866
The center of Pluto,
Mr. Smith,

10:58.950 --> 11:01.118
is made of a substance called
"plutonium."

11:01.202 --> 11:04.830
mines like these suck plutonium
up to the cities,

11:04.914 --> 11:07.124
where corporations use it
to power everything,

11:07.208 --> 11:10.836
from diamond cars
to golden showers.

11:10.920 --> 11:13.839
And the more we remove,
the more Pluto shrinks.

11:13.923 --> 11:15.841
[ rumbles ] There it goes again.

11:15.925 --> 11:17.468
Just shrank a little.

11:17.552 --> 11:18.719
But a few years ago,

11:18.803 --> 11:21.638
your scientists noticed Pluto
had gotten so small

11:21.723 --> 11:23.932
they couldn't even call it
a "planet" anymore.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.809
Should've been
our wake-up call.

11:25.894 --> 11:27.603
But the rich plutonians
won't wake up,

11:27.687 --> 11:30.481
and they love your Dad telling
everyone Pluto's a planet

11:30.565 --> 11:32.524
because that means
they can keep mining

11:32.609 --> 11:35.861
until Pluto goes
from planet to asteroid

11:35.945 --> 11:39.156
to meteor, and finally...

11:39.240 --> 11:41.742
poof.
- Um, a party?

11:41.826 --> 11:43.226
Is everyone in your family
an idiot?

11:43.286 --> 11:44.953
Well, for sure
me and my Dad are.

11:45.038 --> 11:46.789
[ sighs ]
Well, all you have to do

11:46.873 --> 11:48.415
is get him to admit that,

11:48.500 --> 11:51.001
and you could save
four billion lives.

11:51.086 --> 11:56.048
Yeah, you know, the thing is
my Dad's really insecure.

11:57.842 --> 11:59.301
Hmm. Funny.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.637
Mr. Needful, out of everything
in the store,

12:01.721 --> 12:04.348
you'll never guess
what we couldn't get rid of.

12:04.432 --> 12:06.350
[ gasps ]
- [ sputtering ]

12:06.434 --> 12:07.976
Oh, my god.

12:08.061 --> 12:10.020
[ grunting ]

12:10.105 --> 12:11.647
Oh, my god.

12:11.731 --> 12:16.318
I wish this desk was lighter.

12:16.403 --> 12:19.405
I wish this knot was looser.

12:19.489 --> 12:21.198
[ grunts ] Come on.

12:21.282 --> 12:23.867
[ blows ] I don't...

12:23.952 --> 12:25.327
[ grunts ]

12:25.412 --> 12:27.037
Wait, what am I doing?

12:27.122 --> 12:29.248
I wish I knew CPR.

12:29.332 --> 12:30.541
1, 2, 3.

12:30.625 --> 12:32.251
[ chokes, sputters ] Oh, Jesus.

12:32.335 --> 12:34.503
What a waste of a monkey paw.

12:34.587 --> 12:36.505
Mr. Needful, how
could you even think of doing

12:36.589 --> 12:38.132
something so horrible?

12:38.216 --> 12:39.800
I'm the devil.
What should I do

12:39.884 --> 12:42.052
when I fail...
get myself an ice cream?

12:42.137 --> 12:43.387
You haven't failed.

12:43.471 --> 12:45.305
People like Rick
are making me obsolete.

12:45.390 --> 12:47.307
I mean, seriously.
I may be "the devil,"

12:47.392 --> 12:50.018
but your grandpa is the devil.

12:50.103 --> 12:51.478
I just want to go back to hell,

12:51.563 --> 12:53.203
where everyone thinks
I'm smart and funny.

12:53.273 --> 12:54.898
No!
It's not fair.

12:54.983 --> 12:57.192
Everyone in this town
got something they wanted

12:57.277 --> 12:58.360
from you... even Rick.

12:58.445 --> 13:01.530
I was your only friend,
and I get nothing?

13:01.614 --> 13:04.491
Okay. I'll give you one thing.
Name it.

13:04.576 --> 13:06.827
I want to help you.

13:06.911 --> 13:07.911
Clever twist.

13:07.912 --> 13:10.080
I learned from
the best, you old fart.

13:10.165 --> 13:12.207
Now, let's go get you hydrated.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.917
Looks like we've got...

13:14.002 --> 13:15.919
haunted boxing gloves
that will make you

13:16.004 --> 13:17.880
the heavyweight champion
in 1936,

13:17.964 --> 13:19.840
and then you'll be
trapped there,

13:19.924 --> 13:21.341
winning the same fight
for eternity.

13:21.426 --> 13:23.302
I can take out the "eternity"
and the padding,

13:23.386 --> 13:26.013
and then you'll have some
time-traveling mittens.

13:26.097 --> 13:28.015
Oh, look, it's Rosemary's Baby.

13:28.099 --> 13:29.725
How's business?

13:29.809 --> 13:31.602
Here's the last
of our inventory.

13:31.686 --> 13:34.563
We're going to file chapter 1 1
and do some restructuring.

13:34.647 --> 13:36.482
Sounds like code for
"You win, Rick."

13:36.566 --> 13:38.442
That was important
to you, wasn't it?

13:38.526 --> 13:40.110
Nope. Lt was important
to your dumb devil friend.

13:40.195 --> 13:41.820
To me, this was all just a bit,

13:41.905 --> 13:43.447
like when Bugs Bunny fucks
with the opera singer

13:43.531 --> 13:44.656
for 20 minutes.

13:44.741 --> 13:46.283
He tried to kill himself.

13:46.367 --> 13:48.535
[ laughing ]
Seriously? Holy crap.

13:48.620 --> 13:50.245
Holy crap.

13:50.330 --> 13:52.039
But you know what, Grandpa Rick?

13:52.123 --> 13:53.999
He's strong, and he's never
going to give up.

13:54.083 --> 13:56.543
- Uh-huh, yeah, I don't care.
- Oh, I know.

13:56.628 --> 13:58.420
- Everyone knows you don't care.
- So?

13:58.505 --> 14:00.422
So have fun not caring.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.174
- I always do.
- Good.

14:02.258 --> 14:04.051
Yeah, it is good.
[burps] It's the best.

14:04.135 --> 14:06.136
I'm sure it is.

14:06.221 --> 14:07.721
- Bye.
- Later.

14:07.805 --> 14:10.140
I'm here to pick up
my undead cat and child.

14:10.225 --> 14:12.392
Yeah, uh...
give me a sec.

14:12.477 --> 14:14.770
These are the forms
for the employee health plan.

14:14.854 --> 14:18.315
All right, yeah, put...
put them on my... eh.

14:18.399 --> 14:20.984
I just got bored.

14:21.069 --> 14:23.654
Everybody out.

14:23.738 --> 14:25.614
JERRY:
All right, just one more rally,

14:25.698 --> 14:27.574
then I promise we'll get back
to your science project.

14:27.659 --> 14:29.243
Dad, Pluto isn't a planet.

14:29.327 --> 14:30.911
It's shrinking because
of corporations.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.913
Yeah, that's what that
anti-planet nut job

14:32.997 --> 14:34.873
Scroopy Noopers was
screaming about

14:34.958 --> 14:37.000
outside the Ministry of Money's
Fundraiser.

14:37.085 --> 14:39.836
Are you telling me four billion
Plutonians are wrong?

14:39.921 --> 14:41.547
You said science wasn't easy.

14:41.631 --> 14:43.257
I said science
isn't a/ways easy.

14:43.341 --> 14:45.842
Obviously, that means
sometimes it is easy.

14:45.927 --> 14:48.053
Let's not debase ourselves
with word games, son.

14:48.137 --> 14:49.555
Dad, their whole
planet is dying.

14:49.639 --> 14:52.933
Ha! You called it a planet.
Checkmate.

14:53.017 --> 14:54.851
What's up, Pluto?

14:54.936 --> 14:56.770
[ cheers and applause ]

14:56.854 --> 14:59.231
[ classical music plays ]

14:59.315 --> 15:01.108
Mr. Smith, please tell
my friend here

15:01.192 --> 15:03.068
what you just told me.
Go on.

15:03.152 --> 15:05.529
My very eager mother
just served us nine pickles,

15:05.613 --> 15:07.489
and the "pickles" is Pluto.

15:07.574 --> 15:10.200
[ sputters ]
My god, the man's a genius.

15:10.285 --> 15:12.119
Um, excuse me.

15:12.203 --> 15:14.204
Morty, what?

15:14.289 --> 15:16.129
Dad, what did you
think about the recent report

15:16.165 --> 15:18.292
published by
The Pluto Science Reader

15:18.376 --> 15:22.838
linking Pluto-quakes, sinkholes,
and surface shrinkage

15:22.922 --> 15:26.383
to deep-core plutonium
drilling?

15:26.467 --> 15:29.636
Well, son, what did you think

15:29.721 --> 15:31.638
when you were five
and you pooped your pants,

15:31.723 --> 15:33.890
and you threw your poopy undies
out your bedroom window

15:33.975 --> 15:35.642
because you thought it was like

15:35.727 --> 15:37.394
throwing something
in the garbage?

15:37.478 --> 15:38.770
[ laughter ]

15:38.855 --> 15:40.135
I mean, I'm trimming the hedges,

15:40.189 --> 15:41.815
and these things are just
hanging there.

15:41.899 --> 15:43.819
Was I supposed to think
the poop bunny left them?

15:43.901 --> 15:46.862
Good one, Dad.

15:46.946 --> 15:49.698
Hey, Morty, you want to
go on a... oh.

15:49.782 --> 15:51.658
Hey, Beth.
Hello?

15:51.743 --> 15:54.119
Hey, Jerry, you in here
being stupid?

15:54.203 --> 15:58.206
[ sighs, burps ]

15:58.291 --> 16:00.000
[ robot whirs ]

16:00.084 --> 16:01.335
Thanks.

16:01.419 --> 16:03.253
Hey, you know, I was thinking,
you know,

16:03.338 --> 16:04.546
I might watch a movie.

16:04.631 --> 16:06.173
I am not programmed for
friendship.

16:06.257 --> 16:08.258
Suit yourself.
[ burps ]

16:08.343 --> 16:11.261
[ hums ]

16:11.346 --> 16:12.429
Hey.
[clears throat] Hey.

16:12.513 --> 16:13.805
W-W-What's going on?

16:13.890 --> 16:17.142
Um, can you help me do
the stupid science fair project?

16:17.226 --> 16:19.102
Whatever.

16:19.187 --> 16:22.397
PLUTONIAN:
Jerry, you must be so excited.

16:22.482 --> 16:25.275
The Pluto-bel prize is
the highest honor

16:25.360 --> 16:27.486
a scientist can receive.

16:27.570 --> 16:29.488
I'm flattered and humbled.

16:29.572 --> 16:32.282
Oh, I like that.
Use that in your speech.

16:32.367 --> 16:34.576
Also, talk about Pluto
being a planet.

16:34.661 --> 16:36.286
People like that.

16:36.371 --> 16:37.954
Your highness, we've captured
Scroopy Noopers.

16:38.039 --> 16:39.581
You animals! Animals!

16:39.666 --> 16:44.294
Ooh, look who's little
journey's come to an end.

16:44.379 --> 16:46.421
Take him to Pluto-namo Bay.

16:46.506 --> 16:49.049
You can't kill the truth,
father.

16:49.133 --> 16:51.343
- What?
- I can see you're confused.

16:51.427 --> 16:53.220
Pluto-namo Bay is
a military prison...

16:53.304 --> 16:55.097
a sort of play on words.

16:55.181 --> 16:56.723
Did he call you "father"?

16:56.808 --> 16:59.267
Scroopy Noopers,
the anti-planet nut job,

16:59.352 --> 17:00.936
is your son?

17:01.020 --> 17:03.271
The young eat the old
if you let them, Jerry.

17:03.356 --> 17:06.483
Pluto is a cold, cold
celestial dwarf.

17:06.567 --> 17:08.735
- It's a what?
- Huh? Oh, planet.

17:08.820 --> 17:10.445
[ laughs ]

17:10.530 --> 17:12.114
"Pluto is a cold,
cold planet."

17:12.198 --> 17:14.116
That's what I meant.

17:14.200 --> 17:17.202
Knock them dead out there, you.

17:18.830 --> 17:22.457
[ echoing ] Pluto is...

17:31.384 --> 17:34.678
[ sighs ] not a planet.

17:34.762 --> 17:37.472
- [ shouting ]
- Ow! It's not a planet.

17:37.557 --> 17:40.851
Hey!
It's not a planet!

17:40.935 --> 17:44.020
I'm an idiot, and I love my son.

17:44.105 --> 17:46.022
It was a long six hours,

17:46.107 --> 17:48.108
but we've overhauled
"Needful Things"

17:48.192 --> 17:49.776
into the globally-compliant
web 4.0

17:49.861 --> 17:53.780
"E-nomenon," n33dful.Com,

17:53.865 --> 17:56.575
spelled with threes
instead of "E's."

17:56.659 --> 17:58.243
[ cheering ]

17:58.327 --> 18:02.539
Okay, that's it.
We just got bought by Google!

18:02.623 --> 18:05.375
Mm.
I'm so proud of you, Lucius.

18:05.460 --> 18:07.878
So, how much did we make?

18:07.962 --> 18:09.921
[ chuckling ]
"We."

18:10.006 --> 18:12.257
This is mybusiness.
Security!

18:12.341 --> 18:14.217
[ gasps ]
You're Zuckerberg-ING me?

18:14.302 --> 18:15.844
I was Zuckerberg-ING people

18:15.928 --> 18:17.554
